---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — TopoQuizz"
  description="Privacy Policy for TopoQuizz. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="privacy-page">
    <div class="privacy-hero">
      <div class="privacy-hero-inner">
        <span class="sec-badge">Legal</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: April 21, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-body">
      <div class="privacy-content">

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>SHEMED YISRAEL SOFTWARE CREATION LLC</strong>
          ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, stores, and shares personal information when you use
          our mobile application <strong>TopoQuizz</strong> (the "App").
        </p>
        <p>
          By using TopoQuizz, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this
          Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          TopoQuizz is a mobile application operated by <strong>SHEMED YISRAEL SOFTWARE CREATION LLC</strong>.
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or about how we process your data, you may contact
          us at: <a href="mailto:administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com">administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2>2. Scope of This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy applies only to the TopoQuizz mobile application and related services directly
          connected to the App. It does not apply to third-party websites, services, or platforms that may
          be linked from within the App.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>3.1 Information You Provide to Us</h3>
        <p>We may collect the following personal information that you voluntarily provide when creating an account or using the App:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Username</li>
          <li>Country</li>
          <li>Gender</li>
          <li>Date of birth</li>
          <li>Login credentials and authentication-related data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Account and Learning Data</h3>
        <p>When you use TopoQuizz, we may collect and store information related to your activity in the App, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Quiz progress</li>
          <li>Scores and results</li>
          <li>Quiz history</li>
          <li>Favorites and saved content</li>
          <li>Selected in-app avatar</li>
          <li>General account preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Social Login Information</h3>
        <p>
          If you choose to sign in through a third-party login provider, such as <strong>Google</strong> or
          <strong>Facebook</strong>, we may receive certain profile information associated with your account,
          depending on the permissions granted by you and the provider. This may include your name, email
          address, and basic profile information.
        </p>

        <h3>3.4 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <p>We may automatically collect certain technical and usage information when you use the App, such as:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Device type and model</li>
          <li>Operating system and version</li>
          <li>App version</li>
          <li>IP address</li>
          <li>Language settings</li>
          <li>Device identifiers</li>
          <li>App usage events and interactions</li>
          <li>Crash logs, diagnostics, and performance data</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To create and manage your account</li>
          <li>To authenticate users and enable secure login</li>
          <li>To provide access to quizzes, progress tracking, and App features</li>
          <li>To personalize the user experience</li>
          <li>To store and display your quiz history, scores, favorites, and selected avatar</li>
          <li>To improve the App, its content, and its functionality</li>
          <li>To monitor usage trends and user engagement</li>
          <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues, fraud, or abuse</li>
          <li>To provide customer support</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
          <li>To display advertising within the App</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          TopoQuizz may display advertising within the App. These advertisements may be served by us or by
          third-party advertising partners. Advertising content may be based on general app usage, device
          information, identifiers, or other data permitted by applicable law.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may use advertising technologies and third-party services to deliver, manage, and measure ads
          shown in the App. These partners may collect certain information automatically, such as device
          identifiers, app interaction data, and diagnostic information, in accordance with their own privacy
          policies and applicable legal requirements.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not knowingly use sensitive personal information for advertising purposes. If we introduce
          more advanced or personalized advertising features in the future, we may update this Privacy Policy
          accordingly.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Third-Party Services and Providers</h2>
        <p>We use third-party service providers to operate and improve the App. These may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Firebase Authentication</strong> — for account authentication and login management</li>
          <li><strong>Firebase Database / Storage</strong> — for storing account and app-related data</li>
          <li><strong>Firebase Analytics</strong> — for analytics and usage insights</li>
          <li><strong>Firebase Crash Reporting / Diagnostics</strong> — for performance monitoring and troubleshooting</li>
          <li><strong>Google Sign-In</strong> — for authentication</li>
          <li><strong>Facebook Login</strong> — for authentication</li>
          <li><strong>Advertising providers</strong> — for displaying and managing ads in the App</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These third parties may process personal information on our behalf or as independent service
          providers, subject to their own privacy notices and applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, we process your personal information based on one or more of the following legal grounds:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your consent</li>
          <li>The performance of a contract or provision of services to you</li>
          <li>Our legitimate interests in operating, improving, securing, and monetizing the App</li>
          <li>Compliance with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. How We Share Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your personal information in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>With service providers that help us operate the App</li>
          <li>With authentication and login providers such as Google and Facebook</li>
          <li>With analytics, diagnostics, and advertising partners</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations, court orders, or lawful requests from authorities</li>
          <li>To protect our rights, users, systems, and business</li>
          <li>In connection with a merger, acquisition, restructuring, asset sale, or similar business transaction</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information in exchange for direct monetary payment in the ordinary
          course of operating the App. However, some data sharing with advertising or analytics providers
          may be considered "sharing" or similar regulated processing under certain laws.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide the App and fulfill the
          purposes described in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or
          permitted by law.
        </p>
        <p>
          In general, we retain account and learning data for as long as your account remains active. If
          your account is deleted, we will delete or anonymize your personal data within a reasonable period,
          except where retention is necessary for legal, security, fraud prevention, or backup purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures designed to protect your personal
          information against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, disclosure, or alteration.
        </p>
        <p>
          However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure.
          For this reason, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          TopoQuizz is not intended for children under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly collect
          personal information from children under 18. If we become aware that we have collected personal
          information from a child under 18 without appropriate authorization, we will take reasonable steps
          to delete such information.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you believe that a child under 18 has provided us with personal information, please contact us
          at <a href="mailto:administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com">administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have certain rights regarding your personal
          information, including the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your information</li>
          <li>Object to or restrict certain processing</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
          <li>Request a copy of certain information in a portable format, where applicable</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You may exercise your rights by contacting us at
          <a href="mailto:administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com">administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com</a>.
          We may need to verify your identity before processing your request.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Account Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          You may request deletion of your account and associated personal data by contacting us at
          <a href="mailto:administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com">administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are also implementing an in-app account deletion feature. Once available, users will be able
          to initiate account deletion directly from within the App.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please note that we may retain certain information where necessary for legal compliance, fraud
          prevention, dispute resolution, security, or enforcement of our rights.
        </p>

        <h2>14. International Data Processing</h2>
        <p>
          Your information may be processed and stored in countries other than your own, including countries
          where our service providers operate. By using the App, you understand and acknowledge that your
          information may be transferred to and processed in jurisdictions with different data protection laws.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our services,
          technologies, legal requirements, or business practices. When we do, we will update the
          "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
        </p>
        <p>
          We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>16. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, you may contact us at:</p>
        <address>
          <strong>SHEMED YISRAEL SOFTWARE CREATION LLC</strong><br />
          4851 W Hillsboro Blvd Ste A3<br />
          Pompano Beach, FL 33073<br />
          United States<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com">administracion@shemayisraelsrl.com</a>
        </address>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer appStoreUrl="#" playStoreUrl="#" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .privacy-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(121deg, #3b4d6d 0%, var(--blue) 60%, var(--blue-mid) 100%);
    padding: 72px 0 64px;
  }

  .privacy-hero-inner {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 80px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .privacy-hero h1 {
    font-family: "Plus Jakarta Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .privacy-hero p {
    color: var(--blue-light);
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .privacy-body {
    padding: 64px 0 96px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .privacy-content {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 80px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .privacy-content p {
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .privacy-content h2 {
    font-family: "Plus Jakarta Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 20px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--blue-pale);
  }

  .privacy-content h3 {
    font-family: "Plus Jakarta Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .privacy-content ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .privacy-content li {
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .privacy-content a {
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .privacy-content a:hover {
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  .privacy-content strong {
    color: var(--navy);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  address {
    font-style: normal;
    background: var(--white);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 2;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(40, 49, 67, 0.05);
  }

  address strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: "Plus Jakarta Sans", sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-hero-inner,
    .privacy-content {
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    .privacy-hero {
      padding: 48px 0 40px;
    }

    .privacy-hero h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
    }

    .privacy-body {
      padding: 48px 0 72px;
    }
  }
</style>
